## ğŸš€ Installation

### Prerequisites

1. **Python 3.8+**
2. **Ollama** (recommended) â€” [Install Ollama](https://ollama.ai)
   ```bash
   ollama pull llama3.2-vision
   ```

### Install Djinn

```bash
# Clone or navigate to the project
cd ghost

# Install globally
pip install -e .

# Verify installation
djinn --version
```

---

## ğŸ“– Usage

### Quick Command

```bash
djinn "list all files larger than 100MB"
```

### Interactive Mode

```bash
djinn -i
```

```
djinn > convert all mov files to mp4
âœ“ Command: for f in *.mov; do ffmpeg -i "$f" "${f%.mov}.mp4"; done
ğŸ“‹ Copied to clipboard!

djinn > refine use parallel processing
âœ“ Command: parallel ffmpeg -i {} -c:v libx264 {.}.mp4 ::: *.mov
ğŸ“‹ Copied to clipboard!
```

### Multi-Language

```bash
# Arabic
djinn --lang ar "Ø£Ù†Ø´Ø¦ Ù…Ø¬Ù„Ø¯ Ø¬Ø¯ÙŠØ¯ Ø¨Ø§Ø³Ù… Ù…Ø´Ø±ÙˆØ¹"

# French
djinn --lang fr "supprimer tous les fichiers temporaires"
```

### View History

```bash
djinn history              # Recent commands
djinn history --favorites  # Favorite commands
djinn history --search "docker"
```

### Configuration

```bash
djinn config --backend ollama     # Set default backend
djinn config --model gpt-4        # Set default model
djinn config --lang ar            # Set default language
djinn config --show               # Show current config
```

---

## ğŸ”§ Backends

| Backend | URL | Setup |
|---------|-----|-------|
| **Ollama** | `localhost:11434` | `ollama serve` |
| **LM Studio** | `localhost:1234` | Start LM Studio with server enabled |
| **OpenAI** | `api.openai.com` | Set `OPENAI_API_KEY` env variable |

```bash
# Use a specific backend
djinn -b lmstudio "find all python files"
djinn -b openai -m gpt-4 "optimize this query"
```

